Adriene, THANK YOU SO MUCH. I've been stuck in a toxic relationship and have been putting my whole existence on hold. I've always wanted to try yoga but always put it on hold. In January, my guy moved for a job and we lived apart for the first time in 11 years. I joined your "HOME" 30 day yoga journey and through the practice of showing up for myself consistently every day, I learned what someone showing up for me ACTUALLY felt like and realized I was not in true supportive partnership. Yoga is not the reason my marriage is ending but it ABSOLUTELY helped me finally respect myself enough to do what is right for me. I am so grateful for you and your 30 day programs and how accessible you have made yoga for me & others. Everything you say seems to be just the medicine I need in the moment. This practice was LOTS of tears of unblocking and gratitude. THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU <3 endless love!

Big hug,

I've long struggled with corpse pose. It has been the most consistently difficult pose for me throughout 10+ years of practice. I have lordosis and when my core is weaker, the compression through the low back is particularly bad. Of late I have realized by margins that part of the problems was clenching and pulling down with the feet thus forcing my back to round so I've been working on freeing that up. Yesterday I stumbled on an image that really transformed the pose for me which was of lying on your back in water. Instead of being a bum, foot affair ft shoulder, head and low back, it became a torso-led experience that finally allowed for relaxation without pushing or bending my low back or actively pressing down with the core. Couldn't have done it without you!

Relish in this therapeutic practice.
